<title>NIGER: Niger yr-on-yr inflation falls to 2.0 pct in June.</title>
<headline>Niger yr-on-yr inflation falls to 2.0 pct in June.</headline>
<dateline>NIAMEY 1997-07-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Consumer prices in Niger rose by 0.8 percent in June compared with May, cutting the year-on-year inflation rate to 2.0 percent from 3.6 percent, the government statistics ddepartment said.</p>
<p>					  June	     May</p>
<p>	Change on month	     +0.8 pct	 +0.7 pct</p>
<p>	Change on year		+2.0 pct	 +3.6 pct</p>
<p>	Index (base 1989 = 100)   155.4	    154.2</p>
<p>The rise in June was due essentially to an increase in the price of food, which rose 1.4 pct, and particularly prices of vegetables and dairy products.</p>
<p>The government is aiming to hold inflation below four percent this year.</p>
<p>-- Abidjan newsroom +225 21 90 90</p>
